

	 
       Hampered hopes on the swinging light  Floating above the precipice and below it,  Falling behind the dampened love    Sweet despair, sweet and tender  Swaying with the clouds, far and yonder  Fragrant vengeance, fragrant and amorous  Praying in the fire, alongside Prometheus    Soaring down to Hades, a lonely  Gone is she, the innocence of Persephone  Burning within the requiem  Is a dangling priest, angry at the loss    Mercy for the souls of the  Weak. For theirs is the kingdom  Where Cerberus lives  Undying and Suffering.    
     
    
